      • setVideoListener

        public static void setVideoListener(MoPubRewardedVideoListener listener)
        Sets the MoPubRewardedVideoListener that will receive events from the rewarded video system. Set this to null to stop receiving event callbacks.

      • loadVideo

        public static void loadVideo(java.lang.String adUnitId,
                             MediationSettings... mediationSettings)
        Builds an AdRequest for the given adUnitId and adds it to the singleton RequestQueue. This method will not make a new request if there is already a video loading for this adUnitId.
        Parameters:
        adUnitId - MoPub adUnitId String
        mediationSettings - Optional instance-level MediationSettings to associate with the above adUnitId.

        Notify the manager that a rewarded video loaded successfully.
        Type Parameters:
        T - - a class that extends CustomEventRewardedVideo. Only rewarded video custom events should use these methods.
        Parameters:
        customEventClass - - the Class of the third-party custom event object.
        thirdPartyId - - the ad id of the third party SDK. This may be an empty String if the SDK does not use ad ids, zone ids, or a analogous concept.
